<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-7932] Corrupt SSTable Cleanup Leak Resources</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7932</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7705&quot; title=&quot;Safer Resource Management&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-7705&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-7705&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, during the BlackingListingCompactionsTest, detected leaks. I&apos;ve tracked this down to DataTracker.removeUnreadableSSTables() , which does not release the reference to any sstables from the tracker.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12741310">CASSANDRA-7932</key>
            <summary>Corrupt SSTable Cleanup Leak Resources</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
